Why they use Django

Built-in admin panel ‚Üí manage users, posts, reports

Strong security

Handles large databases well

Example

Instagram needs user management, admin control, data validation, and security. Django fits well because it already provides these features out of the box.

Flask ‚Äì Used for Microservices & APIs

Companies:

Netflix

Airbnb

Uber

Why they use Flask

Lightweight

Easy to create APIs

Good for independent services

Example

Netflix uses Flask for internal APIs like recommendation or analytics services where only a small, focused backend is required.

FastAPI ‚Äì Modern High-Performance APIs

Companies:

Microsoft

Uber

Netflix (new services)

Why they use FastAPI

Very fast

Auto API documentation

Great for microservices

Example

A payment or notification service that needs high speed and clear API documentation is perfect for FastAPI.

2. HR-Friendly Answer (Simple & Non-Technical)
Short HR Answer

‚ÄúI have worked with Python frameworks like Django and Flask. Django is best for full-scale applications with built-in features like admin and authentication, while Flask is lightweight and used mainly for APIs and microservices. Recently, FastAPI is preferred for high-performance APIs.‚Äù

Slightly Detailed HR Answer

‚ÄúDjango is a full-stack framework that helps build complete applications quickly. Flask gives more flexibility and is mainly used for smaller services and APIs. FastAPI is a modern framework designed for fast and scalable APIs with automatic documentation.‚Äù

3. Flask vs Django vs FastAPI (Simple Comparison)
Feature	Django	Flask	FastAPI
Type	Full-stack	Micro-framework	API-focused
Speed	Medium	Medium	Very fast
Admin panel	Yes	No	No
ORM	Built-in	Optional	Optional
API docs	Manual	Manual	Auto-generated
Best use	Large apps	Small apps & services	High-performance APIs
